  JOHANNESBURG - Geraldine Fraser-Moleketi, who was minister of Public Service and Administration from 1999 to 2008, says strike action should always be a last resort, and in this case, unions have failed the public. Patients were severely inconvenienced at some hospitals, with workers leaving their posts, and taking to the streets. READ: Nehawu must go back to negotiating table - analyst Meanwhile, President Cyril Ramaphosa says he is concerned about the ongoing wage strike that is affecting essential services. Ramaphosa says while workers have a right to strike, acts of violence will not be tolerated. The strike action to demand a 10 percent wage increase has spread across the country. Geraldine Fraser-Moleketi speaks to #eNCA. Courtesy #DStv403